    Performs Canonical Correlation Analysis using Empirical Orthogonal Functions from a lagged dataset using a dataframe

    cancor_eof.data.frame.Rd

    Performs CCA using EOF analysis using in a dataframe

    Usage

    # S3 method for data.frame
cancor_eof(x, lag = 7, n_eof = 10, values_df, ...)

    Arguments

    x

    The dataframe or stars object. If it is a dataframe, then it should have the locations.

    lag

    Specifies the lag to be used.

    n_eof

    The number of EOFs to be used.

    values_df

    The dataframe of dimension length(times) x length(locations) containing the quantity of interest.

    ...

    Other arguments that need to be used for datafames or currently ignored.

    Examples

    cancor_eof(x = SSTlonlatshort,
           lag = 7,
           n_eof = 8,
           values_df = SSTdatashort)
